cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.LG 

The paper deals with the problem of identifying curve patterns on cultural heritage objects, which involves image processing and pattern recognition. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves geometric modeling and graphics, which suggests the possibility of cs.GR (Computer Graphics). The use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for re-ranking the candidate matchings indicates the possibility of cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also involves machine learning, which suggests the possibility of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
